# Catalyst One Development Policy

Status: **OFFICIAL** (permanent)

Vercel is the continuous review platform.  
GitHub is permanent source-control history.  
These two workflows remain **independent**.

## Workflow (repeat Steps 1–4 for each approved implementation)

### 1. IMPLEMENT
Implement the requested feature or improvement.

### 2. VALIDATE
Ensure the implementation is stable and follows all Enterprise Standards (build, TypeScript, critical lint, relevant smoke checks).

### 3. DEPLOY TO VERCEL
Deploy the latest implementation **immediately** for business review.

- **No Git commit required**
- **No Git push required**
- Deploy from the local working tree unless the user directs otherwise

### 4. REPORT
Inform the user of:

- What was changed
- Which files were modified
- Any architectural decisions
- Vercel deployment status (+ latest URL)
- Business & Functional Certification Report (see `business-functional-certification-report.mdc`)

### 5. ITERATE
Continue implementing further feedback. Repeat Steps 1–4 as many times as necessary.

### 6. GIT COMMIT / PUSH
Only perform Git commit and Git push when **one** of the following occurs:

- The user **explicitly** asks for it
- A **major certified milestone** is completed
- **End of development session** (when the user indicates the session is ending)
- **End of business day** (when the user indicates end-of-day)

Git history must contain **clean, meaningful milestones** — not every UI refinement.

## Defaults (unless instructed otherwise)

| Action | Default |
|--------|---------|
| Deploy to Vercel after every approved implementation | ✔ Yes |
| Commit / push to GitHub automatically | ✘ Never |

## Manual / infra disclosure

If any implementation needs a database migration, schema change, environment variable update, or other manual ops step, **state it explicitly** before claiming the work is complete.
